<title>Google looks set to join the 'buy' button trend</title>
<pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2015 17:50:11 -0700</pubDate>
<author>Zach Miners</author>
<dc:creator>Zach Miners</dc:creator>
<description>
<![CDATA[
<article> <section class="page"> <p>Google will include a “buy” button in its search results on mobile devices in the coming weeks, said a report on Friday in the Wall Street Journal, a move that could give online shoppers an easier way to buy products on small screens.</p><p>The change might a
]]>
<![CDATA[
lso give consumers an alternative to mobile apps from companies like Amazon and eBay, though it might jeopardize retailers’ ability to directly market to their customers.</p><p>The buy button will appear on Google’s search results pages when people search for certain products on mobile devices, said <a href="http://www.wsj.com/articles/can-google-outsell-amazon-and-ebay-1431730741">the report</a>, which cited unnamed sources. If users click on the buttons, they’ll be taken to another Google page where they can choose among sizes and colors, select shipping options and complete the purchase, the report said.</p><p class="jumpTag"><a href="/article/2923292/google-looks-set-to-join-the-buy-button-trend.html#jump">To read this article in full or to leave a comment, please click here</a></p></section></article>
